# Sufficit Identity STS — Docker build context exclusions.
# See Dockerfile's top comment for the build-context requirements (this repo
# + the sibling sufficit-identity-ui repo as a named "ui" build context).

# --- Secrets: NEVER let these ride into an image layer ---
# Real, untracked, developer-local config (see .gitignore) that can contain
# live DB/RabbitMQ/OAuth credentials (docs/EVALUATION-2026-07-20.md §2 C4).
# The Dockerfile also deletes these defensively after COPY, but excluding
# them here means they never even reach the build context/cache in the
# first place.
**/appsettings.json
**/appsettings.*.json
!**/appsettings.json.template
.env
.env.*
**/*.pfx
**/*.p12
**/*.key

# --- Build artifacts (never needed in the context; slows every build) ---
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/.vs/
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/

# --- VCS / CI / docs (irrelevant to the image, only bloats the context) ---
.git/
.github/
docs/
*.md

# --- Test project (not part of the published STS) ---
src/tests/
